article.description: James Madison 85, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 73
article.headline: James Madison 85, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 73
article.linkText: James Madison 85, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 73
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Terrance Carter scored 20 points and James Madison handed Mount St. Mary's its third loss of the season, winning 85-73 Saturday. The Dukes (3-1) traded baskets with the Mount (0-3) for much of the first half. A three-pointer by Jeremy Goode pulled Mount St. Mary's into the lead 18-16, but was answered by a pair of free throws from Dazzmond Thornton. James Madison's Abdulai Jalloh added two of his 18 points to tie the score 20-20, the first of a game total nine ties. Heiden Ratner added two to push the Dukes ahead 40-38 going into the half. Jalloh set the pace for the second half with a three-pointer early, and the Dukes kept the Mount no closer than five points. Juwann James scored 15 points for the Dukes. Goode had 27 points.
